The paper deals with coding theory and the sum-rank metric, which is a topic in information theory (cs.IT). It also involves the study of lattice structures and characterizations of support spaces, which are topics in discrete mathematics (cs.DS) and signal processing (cs.SI). The applications of the sum-rank metric to linear network coding and the discrete memoryless channel suggest that it may also be relevant to networking (cs.NI) and distributed computing (cs.CC).
